.TH hal-fdi-validate 1M "28 Aug 2006" "SunOS 5.11" "System Administration Commands"
.SH NAME
hal-fdi-validate \- validate HAL device information files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
.nf
\fBhal-fdi-validate\fR  [\fB-f\fR \fIdtd\fR] \fIfile\fR [\fIfile\fR].\|.\|.
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
.LP
The
.B hal-fdi-validate
command validates one or more device information
files. See
.BR fdi (4).
The standard DTD file will be used unless the
.B -f
option is used to specify a different file.
.SH OPTIONS
.sp
.LP
The following option is supported:
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
.B -f
.I dtd
.ad
.RS 10n
.rt
Specify path to a DTD file.
.RE

.SH OPERANDS
.sp
.LP
The
.B hal-fdi-validate
command accepts the following operand(s):
.sp
.ne 2
.mk
.na
\fIfile\fR [\fIfile\fR.\|.\|.]\fR
.ad
.RS 18n
.rt
One or more DTD files to be validated.
.RE

.SH ATTRIBUTES
.sp
.LP
See
.BR attributes (5)
for descriptions of the following attributes:
.sp

.sp
.TS
tab() box;
cw(2.75i) |cw(2.75i)
lw(2.75i) |lw(2.75i)
.
ATTRIBUTE TYPEATTRIBUTE VALUE
_
AvailabilitySUNWhalr
_
Interface StabilityVolatile
.TE

.SH SEE ALSO
.sp
.LP
.BR hald (1M),
.BR fdi (4),
.BR attributes (5),
.BR hal (5)
